Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @cucumber{1/2}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the cucumber, stopping at the seeds.

In a #large bowl{}, mix together the @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tbsp}(for the pickle) and a pinch of @salt{}. Add the cucumber ribbons to the bowl and mix to coat the cucumber in the pickling liquid.

Meanwhile, trim the @spring onion{1}, then halve widthways. Slice each half lengthways down the middle, then into long thin matchsticks.

> TIP: This method of preparing veg is called a 'julienne' cut!

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into another #bowl{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle in the @Chinese five spice{1%tsp}. Mix to combine.

Season the @THIS™ Isn't Chicken Plant-Based Pieces{170%g} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Dip the pieces into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring they're completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the THIS™ Isn't Chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins.

Once hot, carefully add the THIS™ Isn't Chicken pieces into the pan and fry until golden-brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Meanwhile, place the @bao buns{4} (2 per person) onto a clean plate and microwave, 750W ~{1%minute 30 seconds}, 900W ~{1%minute}.

If you don't have a #microwave{}, place them onto a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until warm and fluffy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, pop the bao buns onto your #plates{}.

Spread the inside of each with some @mayonnaise{32%g} and add the THIS™ Isn't Chicken pieces. Drizzle over the @hoisin sauce{64%g} and tuck in some cucumber ribbons and spring onions.

To finish, drizzle the @sambal paste{15%g} over the top (add less if you'd prefer things milder).

Serve your ultimate bao buns with the fries and remaining cucumber ribbons on the side.

Enjoy!